Table 1. Performance comparisons in terms of top-1 accuracy on 
three standard FGVC benchmarks: CUB-200-2011, Stanford Cars 
and FGVC-Aircraft.

Table 1. Our method achieves competitive performance 
compared to the prior CNN-based and Transformer-based 

methods. Particularly, with the R50-ViT-Base backbone, 
DCAL reaches 92.0%, 95.3% and 93.3% top-1 accuracy on 
CUB-200-2011, Stanford Cars and FGVC-Aircraft bench-
marks, respectively.

FGVC in terms of accuracy. SA: using SA as the last layer to

Table 6. Ablation study on different inference architectures for 
object Re-ID in terms of mAP and rank-1 accuracy. SA: using SA 
as the last layer to output final feature. GLCA: using GLCA as the 
last layer to output final feature. SA+GLCA: combine the output 
of SA and GLCA for inference.
